== 新闻 ==
在《[[无国界记者|无国界记者]]》每年发布的“[[新闻自由指数|新闻自由指数]]”排名中，朝鲜的排名始终处于低位。从2002年到2006年，该国的新闻自由指数极低，从2007年到2016年，它在约180个国家中排名倒数第二（仅次于[[厄立特里亚|厄立特里亚]]）。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Worldwide press freedom index|url=http://en.rsf.org/spip.php?page=classement&id_rubrique=1001|accessdate=2008-01-09|work=Reporters Without Borders|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120128213104/http://en.rsf.org/spip.php?page=classement&id_rubrique=1001|archivedate=2012-01-28}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=World Press Freedom Index|url=http://www.voanews.com/content/backgrounderembedded/2639867.html|accessdate=2015-02-12|work=Voice of America|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305160138/http://www.voanews.com/content/backgrounderembedded/2639867.html|archivedate=2016-03-05}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=Map|url=https://rsf.org/en/ranking/2016|accessdate=2016-04-21|date=2014|work=2014 World Press Freedom Index|publisher=Reporters Without Borders|archive-date=2017-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170314000216/https://rsf.org/en/ranking/2016|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|title=Map|url=https://rsf.org/en/ranking/2016|accessdate=2016-04-21|date=2016|work=2016 World Press Freedom Index|publisher=Reporters Without Borders|archive-date=2017-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170314000216/https://rsf.org/en/ranking/2016|dead-url=no}}</ref>在2017年和2018年，朝鲜再度排名最差。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=North Korea|url=https://rsf.org/en/north-korea|accessdate=2017-04-28|date=2017|publisher=Reporters Without Borders|archive-date=2017-04-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170426113250/https://rsf.org/en/north-korea|dead-url=no}}</ref>在2019年，它被评为倒数第二，高于[[土库曼斯坦|土库曼斯坦]]。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=2019 World Press Freedom Index {{!}} RSF|url=https://rsf.org/en/ranking/2019|work=Reporters Without Borders|access-date=2021-02-24|archive-date=2019-08-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823155223/https://rsf.org/en/ranking/2019|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2020年，它再度名列最后。 <ref name="wpf-2020" />

担任朝鲜记者，必须具有大学学历。经过极其严格的意识形态审查和背景检查后，才可能得到学院院长和管理人员之推荐。实习记者一般会经历4到5年的试用期，评估合格后才能成为正式记者。

在朝鲜，新闻工作是维护，捍卫，拥护和捍卫国家领袖的工作。由于该职业被定义为是政治活动家和动员群众的战士，因此朝鲜的记者必须是纯正的[[金日成|金日成]]主义者和热心的政治活动家，具有战争通讯员的精神和政治资格。朝鲜的记者不断受到“[[洗腦|再教育]]”。

负责朝鲜新闻工作者再教育的组织是“[[朝鲜记者同盟|朝鲜记者同盟]]”。它是记者和政治思想教育组织中等级最高的组织。该组织为记者进行哲学，经济学，世界历史，世界文学和外语方面的培训。

谈及朝鲜国内矛盾被视为叛国，是朝鲜社会的敌人。与金正日崇拜相关的内容在朝鲜中央电视台（广播电台）报道内容占比高达70%。其余内容用于指责美日韩三国。

朝鲜的记者需要写有关金日成家族的文章。金正日过去常用不同的角度惩罚写信人，理由例如“用言语描述一个人的想法”。 <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.naver.com/sol6915/20038438980|title=North Korea controls over foreign countries' press|date=2007-06-20|language=ko|accessdate=2021-02-24|archive-date=2015-05-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518081345/http://blog.naver.com/sol6915/20038438980|dead-url=no}}</ref>

经过再教育，工作15年以上且做出重大贡献的新闻工作者会得到“杰出新闻工作者”称号。 <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://blog.unikorea.go.kr/4700|title=What would be the role of the journalist in North Korea, the country remarked as the lowest in Freedom of Press?|publisher=Seunguk Baek|accessdate=2014-12-20|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150419052215/http://blog.unikorea.go.kr/4700|archivedate=2015-04-19}}</ref>

== 网络政策 ==
2006年，《[[无国界记者|无国界记者]]》互联网部门负责人朱利安·佩恩（Julien Pain）将朝鲜称之为世界上最严重的互联网黑洞， <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/23/technology/23link.html|work=The New York Times|title=The Internet Black Hole That Is North Korea|date=2006-10-23|accessdate=2021-02-24|archive-date=2019-04-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190424144350/https://www.nytimes.com/2006/10/23/technology/23link.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>为列于《互联网敌人》名单之中。 <ref name="List of the 13 Internet enemies">{{Cite web|title=List of the 13 Internet enemies|url=http://www.rsf.org/article.php3?id_article=19603|accessdate=2008-01-09|work=Reporters Without Borders|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080102084750/http://www.rsf.org/article.php3?id_article=19603|archivedate=2008-01-02}}</ref>

朝鲜通常不允许国民访问互联网。仅部分高级官员可以访问。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=Freedom of the Press: North Korea|url=http://www.freedomhouse.org/report/freedom-press/2013/north-korea|accessdate=2014-07-15|work=Freedom House|archive-date=2014-07-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140707210657/http://www.freedomhouse.org/report/freedom-press/2013/north-korea|dead-url=no}}</ref>在大多数大学中，只设置了少量受到严格监控的计算机。其他公民只能访问该国称之为“[[光明网_(朝鲜)|光明网]]”的内部网络。 <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2014/02/23/north_korea_where_the_internet_has_just_5500_sites.html|title=North Korea: Where the Internet has just 5,500 sites|author=Eric Talmadge|work=Toronto Star|agency=Associated Press|date=2014-02-23|accessdate=2014-07-15|archive-date=2020-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200807103142/https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2014/02/23/north_korea_where_the_internet_has_just_5500_sites.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>光明网由[[朝鮮電腦研究中心|朝鲜电脑研究中心]]开发。 <ref>{{Cite web|title=North Korea exposed: Censorship in the world's most secretive state|url=https://cjfe.org/resources/features/north-korea-exposed-censorship-world%E2%80%99s-most-secretive-state|author=Sedaghat|first=Nouran|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150509050318/http://cjfe.org/resources/features/north-korea-exposed-censorship-world%E2%80%99s-most-secretive-state|archivedate=2015-05-09}}</ref>外国人可以使用[[3G|3G]]网络访问互联网。 <ref name="bbc-20130222">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-21546877|title=North Korea to offer mobile internet access|work=BBC|date=2013-02-22|accessdate=2014-07-15|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111221131/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-21546877|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref name="wp-20130226">{{Cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/worldviews/wp/2013/02/26/instagrams-from-within-north-korea-lift-the-veil-but-only-slightly/|title=Instagrams from within North Korea lift the veil, but only slightly|author=Caitlin Dewey|work=Washington Post|date=2013-02-26|accessdate=2014-07-15|archive-date=2015-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150511100645/http://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/worldviews/wp/2013/02/26/instagrams-from-within-north-korea-lift-the-veil-but-only-slightly/|dead-url=no}}</ref>但是，随着IT行业的发展，朝鲜内网访问量也开始增加。 <ref>{{Cite news|first=Jean H.|author=Lee|title=North Korea's 'Digital Revolution' Under Way|date=2011-07-25|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/25/digital-revolution-north-korea_n_908368.html|agency=Associated Press|accessdate=2011-08-08|archive-date=2016-03-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305031221/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/07/25/digital-revolution-north-korea_n_908368.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2014年朝鲜开发的基于[[Android|Android]]系统的[[三池淵_(平板電腦)|三池渊平板电脑]]具有高强度的监控功能。平板电脑会获取用户打开的应用程序截图并保存历史记录。 <ref name="38north-20170303">{{Cite news|url=http://38north.org/2017/03/mwilliams030317/|title=All That Glitters Is Not Gold: A Closer Look at North Korea's Ullim Tablet|first=Martyn|author=Williams|publisher=U.S.-Korea Institute, Johns Hopkins University School of Advanced International Studies|work=38 North|date=2017-03-03|accessdate=2017-03-06|archive-date=2020-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201223091354/https://www.38north.org/2017/03/mwilliams030317/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

